# src/ — PHP Custom MVC Backend

## Purpose
Core PHP backend handling: auth, products, stores, cart, orders, reviews, auctions (seller side).
Entry point: /public/index.php → instantiates Application → matches routes → dispatches to controllers.

## Framework
Custom PHP 8.3 MVC (no Composer framework). Core lives in src/core/.

## Directory Map
```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── controllers/   Request handlers. BaseController provides json(), view(), redirect() helpers.
│   ├── models/        Empty (models not implemented — repo pattern used instead)
│   ├── repository/    Data access layer — raw PDO queries to PostgreSQL
│   ├── services/      Business logic layer (called by controllers, calls repositories)
│   └── views/         PHP template files (Blade-like, rendered by View.php)
├── config/
│   └── database.php   Returns PDO config from $_ENV vars (POSTGRES_HOST, DB, USER, PASSWORD)
├── core/
│   ├── Application.php   Main router/dispatcher — ALL PHP routes defined here (lines 71-163)
│   ├── Router.php         HTTP method + path matching
│   ├── Database.php       Singleton PDO connection
│   ├── Auth.php           Session-based auth helper (uses Redis sessions)
│   ├── Cache.php          Redis caching wrapper
│   └── View.php           Template rendering
└── lib/
    └── ValidationException.php
```

## PHP Route List (Application.php:71-163)
- Auth:      GET/POST /login, /register, POST /logout, GET /profile
- Products:  GET /products, /product, /store
- Cart:      POST /cart/add, /cart/update, /cart/remove, GET /cart/count
- Orders:    GET /orders, POST /checkout, /orders/checkout, GET /orders/show, POST /orders/confirm-received
- Reviews:   GET /reviews/get, POST /reviews/submit, PUT /reviews/update, DELETE /reviews/delete, GET /reviews/images
- Seller:    GET /seller/products, /seller/orders, /seller/reviews
- Auctions:  GET/POST /seller/auctions/*, /seller/auctions/:id/*, /seller/auctions/:id/bids
- Chat:      GET /api/chat/*, POST /api/chat/*

## Key Services
- AuthService        — login, register, session management
- ProductService     — CRUD, search, filtering
- CartService        — add/update/remove cart items
- BuyerOrderService  — checkout, order status for buyers
- SellerOrderService — approve/reject orders for sellers
- ReviewService      — submit/update/delete reviews + images (complex, 30KB)
- AuctionService     — seller-side auction management
- NotificationService— calls Node internal API to trigger push notifications
- FileService        — handles file uploads to ./storage/

## Sessions
Redis-based PHP sessions (session.save_handler=redis, configured via REDIS_HOST/REDIS_PORT).
Auth state: $_SESSION['user_id'], $_SESSION['role'] (BUYER/SELLER/ADMIN).

## Database Connection
src/core/Database.php — singleton PDO. Uses config from src/config/database.php.
Falls back to hardcoded defaults: host=db, db=nimonspedia, user=nimonspedia_user.
